        "summary": "Imam Ja'far al-Sadiq (AS) succinctly describes the three forms of rest: sleep for the body, speech for the soul, and silence for the intellect. This tripartite teaching, delivered in the assembly of 368 AH, reflects Islamic wisdom about the holistic balance of human faculties and the need to attend to each dimension of the self.",
        "key_terms": {
          "النوم": "Sleep — rest of the physical body",
